The paper deals with signal recovery and estimation, which are common topics in information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SP). The use of side information is a key aspect of the paper, which suggests a potential fit with the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also presents numerical evidence and empirical results, which could place it in the sub-categories of multimedia (cs.MM) or social and information networks (cs.SI).
